parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden acceleration can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly without warning
often when applying the brake pedal or when shifting gears. The engine RPMs may increase rapidly
and the vehicle may lurch forward or stall.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intermittent acceleration failure can cause the vehicle to stall or hesitate, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or fails to accelerate when the accelerator pedal is pressed
often resulting in a loss of power or stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Uncontrolled acceleration can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates rapidly and uncontrollably
often without warning
and may be difficult to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Erratic acceleration can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates erratically
often with sudden surges or hesitations
making it difficult to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the non-deployment of airbags in the event of an accident, resulting in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag light is illuminated on the dashboard
the airbag system malfunctions
the airbag sensor is defective
the airbag control module needs to be replaced
the airbag system is faulty
the airbag light comes on without an accident or mishap.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping or hesitation can cause the vehicle to jerk, lurch, or fail to accelerate, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially when merging into traffic or navigating intersections.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks or lurches when shifting gears
hesitates to accelerate
fails to accelerate when pressing the accelerator
or accelerates suddenly and excessively.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause accidents, especially when the vehicle is in reverse or when the driver is attempting to slow down or stop.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly
sometimes without pressing the accelerator
or accelerates excessively when pressing the accelerator.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Problems with clutch or transmission engagement can cause the vehicle to jerk, lurch, or fail to accelerate, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks or lurches when shifting gears
hesitates to engage into gear
or fails to accelerate when pressing the accelerator.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Interference between the brake and throttle systems can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and unexpectedly when applying the brakes
or the engine revs up when pressing the brake pedal.
